{"session_id":"svc-1778009601289764343","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-05T19:33:25.461790662Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-f1e12904-20260505T193318-22288952","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260505T193318-22288952/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260505T193318-22288952/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260505T193318-22288952/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260505T193318-22288952/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260505T193318-22288952/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 2. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-f1e12904\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ereview: cost cap + reviewer routing/downgrade + refusal contracts\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Review sessions have no cost cap enforcement, no reviewer routing policy, and no structured refusal contracts. Without these, a review session can run unbounded cost, use an unavailable reviewer, or fail with an unstructured error that the frontend cannot surface to the operator.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/server/review_session.go (from ddx-e7b80a50, a dep): ReviewSession has max_billable_usd field but no enforcement code.\u0026#xA;- No reviewer routing logic exists in the server review path — preferred_reviewer from Story 17 and the escalation ladder from Story 10 are not consulted.\u0026#xA;- No structured refusal error codes exist (PROMPT_BUDGET_EXCEEDED, COST_CAP_EXCEEDED, REVIEWER_UNAVAILABLE).\u0026#xA;- ddx-0e5c3005 (reviewer routing contract, a dep) must land first.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Enforce max_billable_usd per session: before each turn, check cumulative cost_usd against max_billable_usd; if exceeded, return COST_CAP_EXCEEDED refusal.\u0026#xA;- Reviewer routing: consult Story 17\u0026#39;s preferred_reviewer first; fall back to Story 10\u0026#39;s escalation ladder.\u0026#xA;- Downgrade routing: when preferred reviewer is unavailable, downgrade to next ladder rung and emit review-pairing-degraded event.\u0026#xA;- Implement three structured refusal error codes as typed errors with structured JSON body.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Turn dispatcher implementation (ddx-f7c3d512, a dep).\u0026#xA;- Frontend display of refusal codes (handled by review panel bead).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. max_billable_usd enforced per session: turn rejected with COST_CAP_EXCEEDED when cumulative cost_usd would exceed limit.\u0026#xA;2. Reviewer routing consults Story 17 preferred_reviewer first, then Story 10 escalation ladder.\u0026#xA;3. Downgrade routing: unavailable preferred reviewer falls back to next ladder rung with review-pairing-degraded event.\u0026#xA;4. Three refusal codes implemented: PROMPT_BUDGET_EXCEEDED, COST_CAP_EXCEEDED, REVIEWER_UNAVAILABLE.\u0026#xA;5. TestReview_CostCap_ReturnsCostCapExceeded verifies enforcement at max_billable_usd.\u0026#xA;6. TestReview_ReviewerUnavailable_Downgrades verifies downgrade path and event.\u0026#xA;7. TestReview_RefusalCodes_HaveStructuredBody verifies all three codes return JSON body.\u0026#xA;8. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/server/... green.\u0026#xA;9. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, story:18, area:server, kind:feature\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-42b917fe\" base-rev=\"a8b2f4f630f0636d0645d1c50d8f2d4053a93ca3\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260505T193318-22288952\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260505T193318-22288952","base_rev":"a8b2f4f630f0636d0645d1c50d8f2d4053a93ca3","bead_id":"ddx-f1e12904","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260505T193318-22288952","correlation_id":"ddx-f1e12904:20260505T193318-22288952","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260505T193318-22288952/prompt.md","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-cc813e27","worker_id":""}}}
